        From September 30 to November 9, 2021, the Korea Foundation (KF) presents Creating Connections, a special exhibition celebrating the KF’s 30th anniversary. This exhibition looks back on the past
        30 years of the KF’s role as a bridge that connects Koreans to the people of the world, and visualizes the foundation’s goals to create new and diverse forms of connections and contribute to a
        better world.

        The collaborative presentation of contemporary artworks that integrate graphics, installation, video, digital and 3D printing, and the metaverse by Korean artists Jin Dallae & Park Woohyuk
        (group), Jun Sojung, Jung Jihyun, and Our labour (group) is also meaningful. Their works offer a synesthetic experience and multi-layered meanings of the various relationships and connections
        between humans, between a nation and the world, between the past and the present, and between reality and virtual reality. Visitors will learn about diverse means of and perspectives on
        exchange and communication.



